module.exports = {"title":"Ruby String Concatenation","date":"2010-01-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"ruby,strings","__content":"<p>I keep finding myself looking up how to concatenate strings in Ruby so I&#39;m writing it down here to help me remember.</p>\n<p>One way (which is familiar to me because its how I would do the same in <a href=\"http://www.php.code-experiments.com/blog/\">PHP</a>):</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\nblah=\"\"\n(1..9).each {\nblah = blah + \"barf\"\n}\nputs blah\n</pre>\n\n<p>A ruby way:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\nblah=\"\"\n(1..9).each {\nblah << \"barf\"\n}\nputs blah\n</pre>\n\n"}

