module.exports = {"title":"Bug in Ruby s XSLT Binding","date":"2010-01-31T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"bugs,ruby,xsl","__content":"<p>I might have found a bug in Ruby&#39;s XSLT bindings:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_ruby\">\nrequire 'rubygems'\nrequire 'rake'\nrequire 'xml/xslt'\n\ntask :default => :some\n@mybuild = 'dkjfh'\n\ntask :some do\n  publish('blah')\n  publish('blah')\nend\n\ndef publish(ok)\n  xslt = XML::XSLT.new()\n  xslt.xml = '<root>ok</root>'\n  xslt.xsl = 'sheet.xsl'\n  hi = { 'dabuild' => @mybuild }\n  new = { 'section' => 'oj', 'subsection' => 'milk' }\n  new.merge!(hi)\n  puts new\n  xslt.parameters = new\n  html = xslt.serve\n  puts html\nend\n</pre>\n\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\n/var/www/dev/ruby-experiments/xslt_prob$ rake\n(in /var/www/dev/ruby-experiments/xslt_prob)\nsectionojsubsectionmilkdabuilddkjfh\ndkjfh\nsectionojsubsectionmilkdabuilddkjfh'\nInvalid expression\nruntime error\nEvaluating user parameter dabuild failed\nnil\n</pre>\n\n"}

