module.exports = {"title":"Github Down","date":"2010-02-03T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"github,hosting,outages","__content":"<p><strong>22:30PM</strong></p>\n<p>I&#39;ve come to use Github.com on a daily basis in a lot of what I&#39;ve been working on.</p>\n<p>Now? Their website and services have been down for about 15 minutes. Doh!</p>\n<p>The website is back online, but is reporting that it is temporarily offline.</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\nStorage server temporarily offline. Please try again in a few minutes or contact GitHub.\nfatal: The remote end hung up unexpectedly\n</pre>\n\n<p><strong>23:16</strong></p>\n<p>Back online, yay!</p>\n<p>According to the Github twitter feed, the problem involved a heartbeat monitor which was incorrectly marking back-end machines as down.</p>\n"}

