module.exports = {"title":"Github Down Again","date":"2010-02-09T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"git,github,hosting,outages","__content":"<p>Whoa - this is kind of odd. I was just perusing recent blog posts I made, saw the one about <a href=\"http://www.docunext.com/blog/2010/02/github-down.html\">Github being down</a>, and remembered I wanted to do some software development. I went to visit Github.com and found it to be down again! Eerie.</p>\n<p>I&#39;m not complaining too much about Github&#39;s service though. Although I pay them for some private repositories, its still a rocking cool service, and git itself makes it possible to stay somewhat productive during temporary outages.</p>\n<p>UPDATE: By the time I finished this post, github was back up. Nice!</p>\n"}

