module.exports = {"title":"Notasinatraapp","date":"2010-02-24T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"datamapper,git,memcache,ruby,ruby 1.9,sinatra","__content":"<p>I&#39;m working on a &quot;showcase&quot; sinatra application:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://github.com/docunext/notasinatraapp\">http://github.com/docunext/notasinatraapp</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>So far I&#39;m experimenting with <strong>caching</strong> gems:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Rack::Cache - this is sweet!</li>\n<li>Sinatra::Cache - looks good for a simple solution, but I&#39;m psyched with Rack::Cache</li>\n<li>ESI</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Data storage</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Git</li>\n<li>DataMapper</li>\n<li>Memcache</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Authentication and Sessions</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Rack::Sessions</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Templates</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Builder</li>\n<li>XSL</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Its a fun project! I&#39;m basing it on the cutting edge: Ruby 1.9.1 and Sinatra 1.0a.</p>\n"}

