module.exports = {"title":"Facebook Feed Patent","date":"2010-03-02T00:00:00.000Z","__content":"<p>I should probably post this in the <a href=\"http://www.informedlicensing.com/\">Informed Licensing</a> blog, but this one is about Facebook, so its OK.</p>\n<p>I read recently that Facebook was approved a patent for the functionality they provide as part of the &quot;wall&quot; feed. Granted, getting approved for a patent does not indicate its validity. If I understand correctly, its little more than a filing.</p>\n<p>However, even before the lawsuits commence, I have to wonder... didn&#39;t this exist before they filed?</p>\n<p>More patent websites:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.labs.docunext.com/ip/patents/ip/patents/0\">U.S. Patent Information</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.informedlicensing.com/blog/patents/\">Patents Category @ Informed Licensing</a></li>\n</ul>\n"}

