module.exports = {"title":"Class and Instance Methods","date":"2010-03-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"1.9,classes,methods","__content":"<p>I love the concepts behind object oriented programming, and in my experience Ruby is taking it to another level!</p>\n<p>I&#39;m reading up on object and instance methods and I found this helpful page:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://railstips.org/blog/archives/2009/05/11/class-and-instance-methods-in-ruby/\">Class and Instance Methods in Ruby</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>I&#39;m going to do some more exercises on this topic, including accessors, modules, and the concept of self, so stay tuned! I&#39;m also going to investigate what parts of class and instance methods, if any, have changed in Ruby 1.9.</p>\n<p>This is helpful too:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://blog.jayfields.com/2007/04/ruby-class-methods.html\">http://blog.jayfields.com/2007/04/ruby-class-methods.html</a></li>\n</ul>\n"}

