module.exports = {"title":"PHP LDAP Admin Errors","comments":[{"author":"turk182","email":"dservellon75@yahoo.es","ip":"10.10.2.8","url":null,"date":"04/29/2010 11:35:46 AM","text":"Albert, just delete this: \"=0\"<br/><br/>and restart slapd.<br/><br/>hope this help you, good luck!!\n"},{"author":"Albert","email":"albert.lash@savonix.com","ip":"96.240.136.9","url":null,"date":"05/01/2010 05:46:44 AM","text":"Hi Turk182 - thanks for commenting! I will give it a try and let you know if it works.\n"},{"author":"Albert","email":"albert.lash@savonix.com","ip":"96.240.136.9","url":null,"date":"05/01/2010 09:42:55 AM","text":"Oh yes - I had actually already done that. Worked like a charm!\n"}],"date":"2010-04-06T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"errors,ldap,php","__content":"<p>I&#39;m trying to login to my phpldapadmin installation but I&#39;m getting these errors:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\nE_STRICT: Declaration of AJAXTree::draw_dn() should be compatible with that of PLMTree::draw_dn()\n</pre>\n\n<p>and</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\nerror (a:5:{i:0;s:97:\"E_STRICT: Declaration of AJAXTree::...&lt;TRUNCATED>)\n</pre>\n\n<p>I&#39;m uninstalling it and reinstalling it... that of course didn&#39;t help. This did:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/phpldapadmin/+bug/446669\">https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/phpldapadmin/+bug/446669</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>which points to this diff for /usr/share/phpldapadmin/lib/AJAXTree.php:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://launchpadlibrarian.net/33321446/phpldapadmin.diff\">http://launchpadlibrarian.net/33321446/phpldapadmin.diff</a></li>\n</ul>\n<pre class=\"sh_diff\">\n16c16\n<       protected function draw_dn($dn,$level=0,$first_child=true,$last_child=true) {\n---\n>       protected function draw_dn($dn,$level,$first_child=true,$last_child=true) {\n</pre>\n\n<p></p>\n"}

