module.exports = {"title":"Learning to Build Tests with Ruby","date":"2010-04-24T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"testing","__content":"<p>I&#39;m taking a moment to study up on how to build tests with Ruby. I&#39;m taking a step back and starting with some very simple examples, to make sure I have the concepts down cold!</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_ruby\">\n\nrequire 'test/unit'\n\nclass DoggyTest < Test::Unit::TestCase\n\n    def test_chekit\n        assert \"hi\" == \"hi\"\n    end\n    def test_barkit\n        assert \"bark\" == \"hi\"\n    end\n\nend\n</pre>\n\n<p>What do you know? Before I tried this I didn&#39;t know that test/unit required methods to be prefixed with &quot;test_&quot; to be auto-run.</p>\n<p>You learn something new everyday. I try to, if I can!</p>\n"}

