module.exports = {"title":"Ryan Tomayko s Shotgun A Forking Implementation of Rackup","date":"2010-04-24T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"rack,ruby,unicorn","__content":"<p>Thanks to Nesta, I found out about Shotgun - a Ruby library used for running Rack applications and middleware.</p>\n<p>Its works good, but I prefer using Unicorn. I&#39;ll probably use it when I don&#39;t have access to Unicorn.</p>\n<p>Shotgun was written and is maintained by Ryan Tomayko, who coincidentally wrote an article about Unicorn which is where I found out about it.</p>\n"}

