module.exports = {"title":"GRE Tunnels with iproute","date":"2010-05-23T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"pfsense,tap,tun","__content":"<p>Marco wrote a useful post yesterday about some <a href=\"http://blog.bofh.it/debian/id_379\">less widely known features of iproute</a>.</p>\n<p>I didn&#39;t know about the dummy interface:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\nip link add mydummy type dummy\n</pre>\n\n<p>but I&#39;ve definitely used the tun/tap driver before. I always forget the syntax so I&#39;ll jot it here for reference:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\nip tuntap add dev mytap mode tap user albertlash\n</pre>\n\n<p>Also mentioned is one of my all-time favorite iproute features: GRE tunnels!</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\nip link add blah type gretap remote 192.168.8.1\nip link add barf type gretap help\n</pre>\n\n<p>I&#39;m thrilled that <a href=\"http://www.informednetworking.com/blog/2008/10/gre-tunnels-in-pfsense.html\">pfsense will soon include GRE tunneling support</a>!</p>\n"}

