module.exports = {"title":"CSS3 Transparency Opacity","date":"2010-06-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"css,css3,opacity,transparency","__content":"<p>Its simple enough:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_css\">\n.transp5 {\n    opacity: 0.5;\n}\n</pre>\n\n<p>For browsers without CSS3 support:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_css\">\n.transp5 {\n  filter:alpha(opacity=50);\n    -moz-opacity:0.5;\n    -khtml-opacity: 0.5;\n    opacity: 0.5;\n}\n</pre>\n\n<p>I setup a couple of classes with trans + &quot;the level of opacity&quot;.</p>\n<p>Also, I recently wanted to set a background color to be transparent, but not the text within it. This is also possible in browsers that support rgba (red, green, blue, alpha) color specifiers:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_css\">\n.transp5bg {\n  background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0.50);\n}\n</pre>\n\n"}

