module.exports = {"title":"Still Using Windows 2000","date":"2010-06-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"virtualization","__content":"<p>I have an old copy of Windows 2000 installed in a QEMU image which I&#39;m still planning to use. Now that I&#39;ve finally gotten my hands on a <a href=\"http://www.my-tech-deals.com/blog/2010/06/awesome-laptop-for-wicked-cheap.html\">cheap laptop that supports KVM extensions</a>, (KVM is an advanced version of QEMU with integrated CPU-capabilities, like AMD-V and Intel VT, support) I&#39;m running Windows updates and its cool to learn that Microsoft still has the updates online.</p>\n<p>I&#39;m now wondering if Internet Explorer 6.0 is the most recent version that can run on W2K. I can install Firefox, but apparently Google&#39;s Chrome requires at least Windows XP.</p>\n"}

