module.exports = {"title":"Dovecot and LDAP","date":"2010-06-30T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"courier,dovecot,ldap,openvz","__content":"<p>I&#39;m really itching to switch from Courier to Dovecot for IMAP access. While I&#39;m at it, I&#39;m planning to phase out POP3.</p>\n<p>Instead of MySQL, I want to use LDAP - its lighter and simpler and just as easy to replicate.</p>\n<p>I&#39;ll continue to use Postfix; and that way I can migrate from CDB to LDAP too.</p>\n<p>My plan to switch to Dovecot will likely go like this:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Setup a new openvz container</li>\n<li>Install dovecot and configure it</li>\n<li>Setup LDAP</li>\n<li>Migrate my mail directories</li>\n<li>Re-route my incoming email</li>\n</ol>\n<p>I&#39;ve done this before so it shouldn&#39;t be too bad.</p>\n<p>UPDATE: I&#39;ve done it! Most of my notes are over at the Docunext Wiki, so check &#39;em out:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.docunext.com/wiki/Dovecot\">Dovecot</a></li>\n</ul>\n"}

