module.exports = {"title":"Memcachedb for Voting Polling Systems","date":"2010-07-21T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"sinatra","__content":"<p>I recently setup a polling system for a client and when I was planning the design, I decided to use memcachedb thanks to the atomic increment functionality.</p>\n<p>I&#39;m using Sinatra and Ruby for most web-based applications I develop these days, and I ran into an issue with <a href=\"http://www.docunext.com/wiki/Ruby_Memcache_Client\">marshal data too short</a> in the memcached client, but that was an easy fix.</p>\n<p>I chose memcachedb instead of memcache for the obvious reason that I need the data to be persistent.</p>\n"}

