module.exports = {"title":"Lua Libraries","date":"2010-07-23T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"json,lua","__content":"<p>The one thing I find seriously lacking with Lua is the limited amount of libraries. However, there are some really good ones.</p>\n<p>For example:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://json.luaforge.net/\">JSON4Lua</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://asbradbury.org/projects/lua-discount/\">Lua Discount</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://asbradbury.org/projects/lua-tinycdb/\">Lua Tinycdb</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://luaforge.net/projects/luacurl/\">Lua Curl</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.keplerproject.org/lualdap/\">Lua LDAP</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://luamemcached.luaforge.net/\">Lua Memcached</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>I&#39;m curious about <a href=\"http://keplerproject.github.com/rings/index.html\">Lua Rings</a> but I can&#39;t quite figure it out.</p>\n<p>Certainly one of the more useful libraries is the <strong>file system library</strong>. That should make it very useful for shell scripting.</p>\n<p>And yes! There is an interface to Toyko Tyrant!!</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://github.com/audrencezar/lua-tokyotyrant\">Lua-tokyotyrant</a> (All your database are belong to Mikio.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In fact, it looks like <a href=\"http://1978th.net/tokyotyrant/spex.html#luaext\">Lua is even integrated into Tokyo Tyrant</a>!</p>\n"}

