module.exports = {"title":"Question about XPaths and Javascript","date":"2010-09-12T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"javascript","__content":"<p>I just posted this in response to a question about XPaths and Javascript on Stackoverflow:</p>\n<blockquote class=\"svxlb\"><pre>\nI would look for an XSLT javascript library. Since most modern browsers have built-in XSLT support, and XSLT includes support for XPath, it is possible to use that engine to power your XPath selectors.\n\nPersonally, I&#39;ve used Sarissa and the Glyphix jQuery.xslTransform libraries successfully:\n\n<em> <a href=\"http://jquery.glyphix.com/\">http://jquery.glyphix.com/</a>\n</em> <a href=\"http://dev.abiss.gr/sarissa/\">http://dev.abiss.gr/sarissa/</a>\n\nThis looks interesting too:\n\n* <a href=\"http://johannburkard.de/software/xsltjs/\">http://johannburkard.de/software/xsltjs/</a>\n</pre></blockquote>\n\n"}

