module.exports = {"title":"private method open called for Rack File Class","date":"2010-10-27T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"class,rack","__content":"<p>I&#39;m trying to open a file from with a Ruby Rack extension I wrote called rack-xsl.</p>\n<p>If I try &quot;File.open(...)&quot;, it fails with this error:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_ruby\">\nprivate method `open' called for Rack::File:Class\n</pre>\n\n<p>Instead, I can use the double colon prefix, or colon colon class name, or ::File:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_ruby\">\n      if @options[:reload] == true\n        @xslt     = XML::XSLT.new()\n        refreshxsl = ::File.open(@options[:xslfilename]) {|f| f.read }\n        @xslt.xsl = REXML::Document.new refreshxsl\n      end\n</pre>\n\n<p>Sweet!</p>\n"}

