module.exports = {"title":"Thanks Molly Guard You Rock","date":"2010-10-30T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"systems administration","__content":"<p>Molly Guard just helped my out once again. Big thank you to the developers who created it. :-)</p>\n<p>What is Molly Guard, you ask? It is a guard to protect big red switched from getting turned off, and it has a cool history, actually.</p>\n<blockquote class=\"svxlb\"><pre>\n[University of Illinois] A shield to prevent tripping of some Big Red Switch by clumsy or ignorant hands. Originally used of the plexiglass covers improvised for the BRS on an IBM 4341 after a programmer&#39;s toddler daughter (named Molly) frobbed it twice in one day. Later generalized to covers over stop/reset switches on disk drives and networking equipment. In hardware catalogues, you&#39;ll see the much less interesting description &quot;guarded button&quot;.\n</pre></blockquote>\n\n<p>Thanks: <a href=\"http://www.catb.org/~esr/jargon/html/M/molly-guard.html\">http://www.catb.org/~esr/jargon/html/M/molly-guard.html</a></p>\n"}

