module.exports = {"title":"Software Development as a Team Sport","date":"2010-12-03T00:00:00.000Z","__content":"<p>I love developing software. Its a passion. I engage without much encouragement or convincing, and as such, often pursue my vocation on my own. I&#39;ve previously written about <a href=\"http://www.docunext.com/blog/2008/05/playing-nicely-and-benefitting-without-belonging.html\">these</a> <a href=\"http://www.docunext.com/blog/2008/04/the-people-who-live-on-planet-debian.html\">factors</a>.</p>\n<p>Nowadays my work has taken me to a situation where software development simply has to be a team sport.</p>\n<p>These days I&#39;m working on projects that are scheduled to be completed in less time than a single individual has available. The only solution is to have multiple people, a team, working on the projects.</p>\n<p>Unfortunately, our team does not have enough team members yet, and not surprisingly, our team is getting crabby and defensive.</p>\n<p>Dear <strong>lazyweb</strong>, what advice might you offer?</p>\n"}

