module.exports = {"title":"Code to Purge Varnish Caches","comments":[{"author":"kenya","email":"kenyajamison@ymail.com","ip":"65.125.92.2","url":null,"date":"01/10/2011 04:26:52 PM","text":"how do i use it on a school computer\n"}],"date":"2010-12-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"varnish","__content":"<p>I use this script and the &quot;expect&quot; command line utility to purge Varnish caches on remote systems:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\n#!/usr/bin/expect\nset 1 $argv\nspawn telnet 192.168.1.99 6082\nexpect \"Escape character is '^]'.\"\nsend \"url.purge $1\\n\"\nexpect \"200 0\"\nclose\n</pre>\n\n<p>Cool, huh? Varnish is really great.</p>\n<p></p>\n"}

