module.exports = {"title":"Git Remote Improvements","date":"2011-01-30T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"git","__content":"<p>The git remote sub-command has received some improvements recently:</p>\n<p>Here&#39;s output from a recent version of git-core:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\n# git remote -h\nusage: git remote [-v | --verbose]\n   or: git remote add [-t <branch>] [-m <master>] [-f] [--mirror] <name> <url>\n   or: git remote rename <old> <new>\n   or: git remote rm <name>\n   or: git remote set-head <name> [-a | -d | <branch>]\n   or: git remote show [-n] <name>\n   or: git remote prune [-n | --dry-run] <name>\n   or: git remote [-v | --verbose] update [-p | --prune] [group]\n\n    -v, --verbose         be verbose\n</pre>\n\n<p>And the latest version (or the current version available in Debian Squeeze):</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\n\n# git remote -h\nusage: git remote [-v | --verbose]\n   or: git remote add [-t <branch>] [-m <master>] [-f] [--mirror] <name> <url>\n   or: git remote rename <old> <new>\n   or: git remote rm <name>\n   or: git remote set-head <name> (-a | -d | <branch>)\n   or: git remote [-v | --verbose] show [-n] <name>\n   or: git remote prune [-n | --dry-run] <name>\n   or: git remote [-v | --verbose] update [-p | --prune] [group | remote]\n   or: git remote set-url <name> <newurl> [<oldurl>]\n   or: git remote set-url --add <name> <newurl>\n   or: git remote set-url --delete <name> <url>\n\n    -v, --verbose         be verbose; must be placed before a subcommand\n</pre>\n\n<p>Most useful to me at the moment is the ability to change the URL for remotes, as I recently setup a gitosis server, then decided to change the hostname pointing to it. Thankfully, this makes is super easy.</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\nsudo git remote set-url origin gitosis@git.example.com:mygitproject.git\n</pre>\n\n"}

