module.exports = {"title":"Git Remote Branch Commands","date":"2011-03-04T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"branches,git,remotes","__content":"<p>I&#39;ve been wanting to figure out how to set an existing local branch to track a remote branch for awhile. Here&#39;s how! As well as the command to delete a remote branch.</p>\n<p>To set the a branch to track a remote branch:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\ngit branch --set-upstream mybranch remotes/origin/mybranch\n</pre>\n\n<p>To delete a remote branch:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_sh\">\ngit push origin --delete mybranch\n</pre>\n\n"}

