module.exports = {"title":"A Review of The Rails 3 Way by Obie Fernandez","date":"2011-03-14T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"activerecord,activesupport,rails,ruby","__content":"<p><iframe src=\"http://rcm.amazon.com/e/cm?t=inforbanki-20&o=1&p=8&l=as1&asins=0321601661&ref=qf_sp_asin_til&fc1=000000&IS2=1&lt1=_blank&m=amazon&lc1=0000FF&bc1=000000&bg1=FFFFFF&f=ifr\" style=\"width:120px;height:240px;\" scrolling=\"no\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" frameborder=\"0\" class=\"flrt\"></iframe>\nMy copy of The Rails 3 Way arrived today. I haven&#39;t had a chance to dig into it yet, but it looks great - its heavy.</p>\n<p>It features forewords by David Heinemeier Hansson and Yehuda Katz, and I noted that the larger sections include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>ActiveRecord</li>\n<li>Helpers</li>\n<li>ActiveSupport</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I&#39;m really looking into reading this tome.</p>\n<h4 id=\"routing\">Routing</h4>\n<p>I&#39;m reading the routing section now, and so far its very clear. I&#39;m pleased that routing feels a little bit like Sinatra to me! This is especially nice because the main reason I used Sinatra was because of how simple and light it <em>was</em>, and since then its grown a lot more heavy - all the while Rails 3 got a lot more modular.</p>\n"}

