module.exports = {"title":"The program chromium browse is writing to file data 3 on dev sda1.","date":"2011-03-18T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"power","__content":"<p>The main problem I have with Google&#39;s chromium browser is how much it writes to disk <strong>ALL THE TIME</strong>.</p>\n<p>Seriously, is there any way to reduce Google Chome&#39;s disk activity??</p>\n<p>Besides Google&#39;s chrome, I feel like my laptop is nearing cooler pastures. Right now, the fan is on all the time, and its just too hot.</p>\n<p>I just noticed - on Ubuntu Maverick, laptop-mode-tools is not installed, it uses pm-utils and acpi-support. I just installed laptop-mode-tools, hopefully it will help!</p>\n"}

