module.exports = {"title":"Ruby Get Files In Directory","date":"2011-05-07T00:00:00.000Z","__content":"<p>Using <strong>Ruby</strong>, I am able to get all the files in a directory, I use this code:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_ruby\">\nmyfiles = Dir.glob(\"*\")\n</pre>\n\n<p>To get the files in a certain path, I just include the path before the glob:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_ruby\">\nmyfiles = Dir.glob(\"/var/www/*\")\n</pre>\n\n<p>Since its a glob, I can choose an extension to filter with:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_ruby\">\nmyfiles = Dir.glob(\"*.png\")\n</pre>\n\n"}

