module.exports = {"title":"Git Subversion SVN authentication","date":"2011-07-14T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"subversion","__content":"<p>I am trying out git svn and its working OK, but I&#39;ve hit a snag (not a show stopper): I can&#39;t get my svn credentials to use GNOME&#39;s session manager.</p>\n<p>Otherwise, I am also a little annoyed that I can&#39;t dcommit to the subversion repository if there are unstaged changes to the current tree. As a stopgap measure, I am simply stashing my changes until I make the dcommit.</p>\n"}

