module.exports = {"title":"Machinist on the Test Environment Console","date":"2011-08-03T00:00:00.000Z","__content":"<p>I am using Machinist 2 beta with Rails 3.1 and its working quite nicely. Though its beta, I&#39;ve found it to be working quite well.</p>\n<p>To do some manual <em>&quot;manufacturing&quot;</em>, I use the console, but for that to work, I have to load the test helper:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_terminal\">\nLoading test environment (Rails 3.1.0.rc4)\n>> require \"./test/test_helper.rb\"\n</pre>\n\n<p>For what its worth, here&#39;s a sample of my blueprints.rb file, too:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_ruby\">\n  1 require 'machinist/active_record'\n  2\n  3 Asset.blueprint do\n  4   name { \"Photo Copier\" }\n  5 end\n  6\n  7 BankAccount.blueprint do\n  8   name { \"National Bank\" }\n  9   number { 12345 }\n 10 end\n</pre>\n\n"}

