module.exports = {"title":"Perl Foreach Array","date":"2011-08-07T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"perl","__content":"<p>Perl has all these funky magic vairables, like $_. Its tough because they are useful with foreach loops, like this one:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_perl\">\nforeach (@myarr) {\n     print $_;\n}\n</pre>\n\n<p>An expanded example:</p>\n<pre class=\"sh_perl\">\n  1 my @x = [];\n  2 $xa = \"a, b, c,d\";\n  3 @x = split(/[,]\\ ?/, $xa);\n  4 foreach $item (@x) {\n  5   $key = $item;\n  6   if($key eq 'c') {\n  7     print $key;\n  8     print \"\\n\";\n  9   }\n 10 }\n</pre>\n\n"}

