module.exports = {"title":"Ruby 1.9.3 and Rails 3.1.1","date":"2011-10-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":"ruby,ruby 1.9","__content":"<p>Tired of waiting for Rails 3 to start up again and again, I decided to try out Ruby 1.9.3-rc1. To my surprised, Ruby 1.9.3-rc1 works reliably well!</p>\n<p>The great part about this is how much faster Rails 3 starts up when using Ruby 1.9.3. Its like night and day.</p>\n<p>I am keeping 1.9.2 installed, and thankfully its not too much of a burden since I&#39;m using rbenv (similar to rvm).</p>\n<p>Let&#39;s go to the races!</p>\n<h4 id=\"the-simplest-race-a-rake-task-\">The Simplest Race (A Rake Task)</h4>\n<pre class=\"sh_ruby\">\nnamespace :speed do\n  task :check => :environment do\n    puts \"Testing...\"\n  end\nend\n</pre>\n\n<h4 id=\"ruby-1-9-2-p290\">Ruby 1.9.2-p290</h4>\n<pre class=\"terminal\">\ntime rake speed:check\nreal    0m44.346s\nuser    0m42.215s\nsys     0m1.416s\n</pre>\n\n<h4 id=\"ruby-1-9-3-rc1\">Ruby 1.9.3-rc1</h4>\n<pre class=\"terminal\">\ntime rake speed:check\nreal    0m12.646s\nuser    0m11.749s\nsys     0m0.784s\n</pre>\n\n<p>Awesome!!</p>\n"}

